    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "weapon",
        "text": "The tetsubo is a war club constructed out of heavy wood shod with iron studs, designed for smashing through armor and defenses. A tetsubo made entirely out of metal might also be referred to as a kanabo.",
        "level": 0,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Razing",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 488,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        },
                        "page": 274,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "1.1",
                            "alt": "1.1",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "1e43c7605c9909b20b487f7dd05b5cee",
                "text": "Razing weapons are particularly good at damaging objects, structures, and vehicles. Whenever you deal damage to an object (including shields and animated objects), structure, or vehicle with a razing weapon, the object takes an amount of additional damage equal to double the number of weapon damage dice.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "shields",
                        "alt": "shields",
                        "href": "Shields.aspx"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "animated objects",
                        "alt": "animated objects",
                        "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                        "aonid": 360
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Shove",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 193,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 283,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "6cd7af0b11cadecab9bad5582f02196b",
                "text": "You can use this weapon to Shove with the Athletics skill even if you don\u2019t have a free hand. This uses the weapon\u2019s reach (if different from your own) and adds the weapon\u2019s item bonus to attack rolls as an item bonus to the Athletics check. If you critically fail a check to Shove using the weapon, you can drop the weapon to take the effects of a failure instead of a critical failure.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Sweep",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 194,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 283,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "435cbfa8d6a3da2e6b53b01082b49f7d",
                "text": "This weapon makes wide swinging attacks. When you attack with this weapon, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack roll if you already attempted to attack a different target this turn using this weapon.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
